#23522
Approaching the Pond~
   The cobblestones abruptly end as a tightly packed, dirt path continues
forward.  The mist has turned some of the dirt into mud, but the footing
remains secure.  Ahead, the mists seem to part revealing a small body of
water.  The thorny bush walls lining the pathways extends to encircle the pond
tightly so that there is no way around it.  
~
