#23526
A Mossy Enclave~
   A green carpeted space is filled with the faint, pleasant scent of rain.  
The ground slightly gives way under your steps as the spongy moss compresses
beneath your weight.  The mist isn't as thick in the enclave compared to the
garden proper and small insects and animals can be seen scurrying about.  The
enclave appears to be a rectangular area encased in the same dense plant-life
walling off the garden from the outside world.  
