#23584
Beneath the Surface~
   Beneath the water swims a multitude of life.  Though the liquid is crystal
clear, the movement all about stirs up dirt and silt slightly obscuring the
view.  The pond is deceptively deep given the small circumference of the
surface and gazing down the light quickly fades to blackness.  The deeper the
water, the colder it gets and the once abundant life seems to be scarce.  
~
